main event: Two round white or gray objects were observed in Corpus Christi, Texas on July 21, 1965.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be maneuvering slowly with no observable features, and the maneuvers were erratic, lasting 15-20 minutes.
The objects were not attached to any fast cosmic flight and maneuvered as a balloon would, with no trails or shadows observed.
The objects' flight was in accord with balloon drifting motions, and no radar returns were detected.
The objects disappeared on a heading of 200 degrees.
The dry air aloft and lack of inversions suggested the objects were not conventional aircraft.
sighted object: two round white or gray objects
